</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="10" pageNumber="43" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1437,152,990]" pageId="10" pageNumber="43">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,313,886,912]" pageId="10" pageNumber="43">Remarks</emphasis>
. Among Palaearctic species of 
<taxonomicName box="[697,823,887,912]" class="Insecta" family="Hybotidae" genus="Tachypeza" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="43" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[697,823,887,912]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="43">Tachypeza</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
the new species is comparable with 
<taxonomicName authority="Fallen" authorityName="Fallen" class="Insecta" family="Hybotidae" genus="Tachypeza" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="43" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fuscipennis">
<emphasis box="[1270,1436,887,912]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="43">T. fuscipennis</emphasis>
(Fallén)
</taxonomicName>
. However, 
<taxonomicName box="[395,495,925,950]" class="Insecta" family="Hybotidae" genus="Tachypeza" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="43" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vriesi" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[395,495,925,950]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="43">T. vriesi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[506,606,925,951]" pageId="10" pageNumber="43">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[506,606,925,951]" pageId="10" pageNumber="43" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
differs by the color pattern of legs and by the presence of a black subapical spine on the fore coxae (similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Meigen" authorityName="Meigen" box="[676,910,964,990]" class="Insecta" family="Hybotidae" genus="Tachypeza" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="43" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nubila">
<emphasis box="[676,780,964,989]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="43">T. nubila</emphasis>
(Meigen))
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
